<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td><nobr><a href='posters'><img width=9 height=20 style='margin-right: 10px' border=0 alt='Go back' src='intr/2captions/goback.png'><img border=0 alt='Posters' hspace=0 src='intr/2captions/posters.png'></a></td><td valign=top height=20><img width=19 height=20 align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3toprise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x'><img border=0 alt='Know your roots' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3captions/knowyourroots.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=20 style='background: url(intr/3topleftfill.png) top repeat-x'><img width=20 height=20 hspace=0 src='intr/3topleft.png'></td><td valign=top><img align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3topleftrise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>
<p>
Seventeen posters highlighting Apple Lisa&rsquo;s most notable pros and cons.
With thanks to James Musheno, Tom Stepleton and Andrew Henning.
</p><p>
The posters are meant to be printed in 70&times;50 cm size, although still look good
when scaled down to A3 format. They can be downloaded freely in ready-to-print PDF 
form, I would just <a href='contact'>appreciate a photo</a> if they are printed and hung 
somewhere.
</p>

<br>

<p>
<b><a href='files/posters/Know%20your%20roots%20posters.zip'>Download all 17 posters in a ZIP archive</a></b> (22 MB).<sup><small>*</small></sup>
</p>

<br>

